#, no-wrap
msgid "Requesting Party Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/overview.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "A requesting party token (RPT) is a https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519[JSON web token (JWT)] digitally signed using https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc7515.txt[JSON web signature (JWS)]. The token is built based on the OAuth2 access token previously issued by {project_name} to a specific client acting on behalf of an user\n"
"or on its own behalf.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/overview.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "When you decode an RPT, you see a payload similar to the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/overview.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "```json\n"
"{\n"
"  \"authorization\": {\n"
"      \"permissions\": [\n"
"        {\n"
"          \"resource_set_id\": \"d2fe9843-6462-4bfc-baba-b5787bb6e0e7\",\n"
"          \"resource_set_name\": \"Hello World Resource\"\n"
"        }\n"
"      ]\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"jti\": \"d6109a09-78fd-4998-bf89-95730dfd0892-1464906679405\",\n"
"  \"exp\": 1464906971,\n"
"  \"nbf\": 0,\n"
"  \"iat\": 1464906671,\n"
"  \"sub\": \"f1888f4d-5172-4359-be0c-af338505d86c\",\n"
"  \"typ\": \"kc_ett\",\n"
"  \"azp\": \"hello-world-authz-service\"\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/overview.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "From this token you can obtain all permissions granted by the server from the *permissions* claim.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/authorization_services/topics/service/rpt/overview.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Also note that permissions are directly related with the resources/scopes you are protecting and complete decoupled from\n"
"the access control methods that were used to actually grant and issue these same permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

